HEADWORD: Steelbow goods
<hw>Steel"bow` goods"</hw> <pr>(st⟦emac⟧l"bou` g⟦oocr⟧dz")</pr>.
<fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>Those goods on a farm, such as corn, cattle,
implements of husbandry, etc., which may not be carried off by a
removing tenant, as being the property of the landlord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

